From: Snider <snider@host.uk.com>
Date: Tue, 16 Jun 2026 18:15:40 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 07/10] =?UTF-8?q?lthn(perf):=20decode-capture=20byte-paylo?=
 =?UTF-8?q?ad=20hash=20=E2=80=94=20proves=20no=20frozen=20per-token=20scal?=
 =?UTF-8?q?ars=20+=20reveals=20the=202-token=20structural=20cycle?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

bytesHash (FNV over all inline setBytes payloads per CB) is IDENTICAL across decode tokens => RoPE offset etc. are buffer-driven, not baked host scalars; the two-update replay plan (input-token + offset buffer CONTENT) is sufficient. Also surfaced: decode = 2 CBs/token, a 47-cmd CB byte-identical every token + a small CB alternating 28/27 cmds every other token (intrinsic, present in serial too) — replay must record the cycle + alternate.

Co-Authored-By: Virgil <virgil@lethean.io>
---
 mlx/backend/metal/device.cpp | 16 ++++++++++++++--
 1 file changed, 14 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/mlx/backend/metal/device.cpp b/mlx/backend/metal/device.cpp
index a801e541..ffbfa0a0 100644
--- a/mlx/backend/metal/device.cpp
+++ b/mlx/backend/metal/device.cpp
@@ -573,12 +573,24 @@ void CommandEncoder::end_encoding() {
     lthn_rec_flush_cur();
     if (!lthn_rec_cmds.empty()) {
       size_t binds = 0, byteSets = 0;
+      uint64_t bytesHash = 1469598103934665603ULL; // FNV-1a over ALL inline-byte payloads
       for (auto& c : lthn_rec_cmds) {
         binds += c.buffers.size();
         byteSets += c.bytes.size();
+        for (auto& by : c.bytes) {
+          for (uint8_t bb : by.first) {
+            bytesHash ^= bb;
+            bytesHash *= 1099511628211ULL;
+          }
+        }
       }
-      std::fprintf(stderr, "[decode-rec] cmds=%zu binds=%zu byteSets=%zu\n",
-                   lthn_rec_cmds.size(), binds, byteSets);
+      // If bytesHash VARIES across consecutive decode tokens, some position-
+      // dependent value (prime suspect: RoPE offset) is frozen as a host setBytes
+      // scalar — replay must patch it, not just update the input+offset buffers.
+      std::fprintf(stderr,
+                   "[decode-rec] cmds=%zu binds=%zu byteSets=%zu bytesHash=0x%016llx\n",
+                   lthn_rec_cmds.size(), binds, byteSets,
+                   (unsigned long long)bytesHash);
       lthn_rec_cmds.clear();
     }
   }
